18 (13) All judgments or orders entered pursuant to Code Section 9-11-11.1;
19 (14) All judgments, orders, or rulings in civil actions granting or denying or refusing to
20 grant or deny immunity to one or more parties based upon sovereign, municipal, official,
21 qualified, or judicial immunity established by the United States Constitution or the
22 Constitution, laws, or common law of this state shall have the right of direct appeal under
23 this paragraph, and such right shall be exercised within 30 days of any judgment, order,
24 or ruling. The right of direct appeal under this paragraph shall not be exercised by any
25 one party more than once in any civil action. This paragraph shall not preclude taking
26 an appeal pursuant to any other paragraph in this subsection; and
27 (15) All judgments, orders, or rulings in civil or criminal actions granting or denying or
28 refusing to grant or deny one or more parties' legislative privilege or legislative immunity
29 established by the United States Constitution or the Constitution, laws, or common law
30 of this state shall have the right of direct appeal under this paragraph, and such right shall
31 be exercised within 30 days of any judgment, order, or ruling."
32 SECTION 2.
33 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
